♪At the first watch of the night♪

471
00:31:29,287 --> 00:31:38,847
♪The crescent moon hasn't appeared♪

472
00:31:39,367 --> 00:31:43,728
♪Diao Chan, the beauty♪

473
00:31:44,488 --> 00:31:52,127
♪Walked down the stairs♪

474
00:31:52,127 --> 00:31:59,047
♪Knelt on the dusty ground♪

475
00:32:02,287 --> 00:32:05,047
♪Burn incense♪

476
00:32:05,047 --> 00:32:07,408
♪And worship the moon♪

477
00:32:07,408 --> 00:32:09,968
♪Burn incense♪

478
00:32:09,968 --> 00:32:12,327
♪And worship the moon♪

479
00:32:12,327 --> 00:32:16,287
♪For our love♪

480
00:32:16,287 --> 00:32:19,367
♪Love♪

481
00:32:19,928 --> 00:32:24,327
♪I say for love and affection♪

482
00:32:25,968 --> 00:32:29,327
♪Affection♪

483
00:33:47,408 --> 00:33:48,287
Ms. Gu,

484
00:33:48,847 --> 00:33:49,648
answer the phone.

485
00:33:51,208 --> 00:33:52,047
Ms. Gu,

486
00:33:52,648 --> 00:33:53,488
wake up.

487
00:33:55,287 --> 00:33:56,888
Ms. Gu, are you home?

488
00:33:57,888 --> 00:33:59,968
What's that racket
so early in the morning?

489
00:34:01,367 --> 00:34:02,928
It's so annoying.

490
00:34:04,408 --> 00:34:05,208
Ms. Gu,

491
00:34:05,448 --> 00:34:06,448
are you home?

492
00:34:17,968 --> 00:34:18,808
Young lady,

493
00:34:19,008 --> 00:34:20,808
can you take down that camera?

494
00:34:21,768 --> 00:34:23,727
The sound from that camera is haunting.

495
00:34:24,768 --> 00:34:25,647
Sorry, Madam,

496
00:34:25,688 --> 00:34:26,952
I'll take it down right away.

497
00:34:27,687 --> 00:34:28,127
Sorry.

498
00:34:28,127 --> 00:34:29,368
It's so annoying.

499
00:34:43,768 --> 00:34:44,408
Don't take it down.

500
00:34:45,008 --> 00:34:46,047
If you do, I'll reinstall it.

501
00:34:48,567 --> 00:34:49,488
Liang Daiwen,

502
00:34:49,928 --> 00:34:51,247
you're disturbing the neighbors.

503
00:34:51,567 --> 00:34:53,207
Move back in with me,
and I won't disturb them.

504
00:34:53,567 --> 00:34:54,687
You go off the grid so often,

505
00:34:54,968 --> 00:34:56,167
and I get really worried.

506
00:34:59,647 --> 00:35:00,848
You're just clingy.

507
00:35:01,448 --> 00:35:02,488
Don't make excuses.

508
00:35:03,527 --> 00:35:04,848
Since you know I'm clingy, get up.

509
00:35:05,352 --> 00:35:06,696
I'll take you out for a meal.

510
00:35:25,527 --> 00:35:26,408
I don't feel like eating.

511
00:35:26,768 --> 00:35:27,968
It's all meat. I have no appetite.

512
00:35:31,167 --> 00:35:32,247
There's no cilantro,

513
00:35:32,808 --> 00:35:34,288
and no pointy-nosed animals.

514
00:35:35,832 --> 00:35:36,840
You don't like meat anymore?

515
00:35:39,768 --> 00:35:41,047
Who told you that?

516
00:35:42,848 --> 00:35:43,968
It must've been my mom.

517
00:36:01,488 --> 00:36:02,368
Do you...

518
00:36:08,792 --> 00:36:10,664
Do you remember the first time
we came here?

519
00:36:12,127 --> 00:36:14,127
At that time, I had severe anorexia.

520
00:36:14,848 --> 00:36:15,727
I couldn't eat anything.

521
00:36:16,104 --> 00:36:17,256
I could only drink water.

522
00:36:18,448 --> 00:36:19,567
You fed me that huge rice ball.

523
00:36:20,488 --> 00:36:21,207
I threw up afterward.

524
00:36:24,008 --> 00:36:24,687
Alright, alright.

525
00:36:24,687 --> 00:36:26,488
Are you trying to change the subject?

526
00:36:28,008 --> 00:36:28,448
Fine.

527
00:36:28,607 --> 00:36:30,247
I'll give you two a break.

528
00:36:31,288 --> 00:36:31,768
I'll eat.

529
00:37:20,808 --> 00:37:21,127
Hello?

530
00:37:21,647 --> 00:37:22,167
Liang.

531
00:37:22,768 --> 00:37:23,928
Can you come find me?

532
00:37:24,008 --> 00:37:25,960
My mom's setting me up on a blind date
at People's Square.

533
00:37:25,968 --> 00:37:27,368
I'm about to go crazy.

534
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:34,880
(Marriage ad: Born in 1993,
master's degree, height 168cm)

535
00:37:34,968 --> 00:37:36,288
Mom, stop putting those up!

536
00:37:36,288 --> 00:37:37,727
What are you doing?

537
00:37:37,727 --> 00:37:38,968
Hey!

538
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:41,064
I should be asking you that.

539
00:37:41,096 --> 00:37:42,696
Mrs. Chen introduced you
to such a fine man,

540
00:37:42,728 --> 00:37:43,440
and you rejected!

541
00:37:43,488 --> 00:37:44,399
Are you out of your mind?

542
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:45,920
Instead, you keep that good-for-nothing
at home.

543
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:46,744
Aren't you embarrassed?

544
00:37:46,776 --> 00:37:47,440
I know I am.

545
00:37:47,687 --> 00:37:49,087
What good-for-nothing?

546
00:37:49,087 --> 00:37:50,328
Can you stop this?

547
00:37:50,328 --> 00:37:52,727
Mrs. Guan, she already has a boyfriend.

548
00:37:52,727 --> 00:37:53,687
Please stop it.

549
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:54,792
What nonsense are you spouting?

550
00:37:54,824 --> 00:37:55,440
What boyfriend?

551
00:37:55,928 --> 00:37:57,087
Haven't you had enough hardship?

552
00:37:57,527 --> 00:37:58,527
Are you out of your mind?

553
00:37:58,808 --> 00:38:00,207
Keeping a freeloader at home?

554
00:38:00,288 --> 00:38:00,928
Mrs. Guan,

555
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:02,600
can we talk about this at home?

556
00:38:03,047 --> 00:38:03,848
Which home?

557
00:38:04,488 --> 00:38:05,087
Ask her.

558
00:38:05,527 --> 00:38:06,968
Who keeps a useless man at home

559
00:38:06,968 --> 00:38:08,328
and throws away a house worth millions?

560
00:38:08,647 --> 00:38:09,567
Millions!

561
00:38:09,687 --> 00:38:11,047
I said I don't want to get married.

562
00:38:11,207 --> 00:38:12,527
Then what do you want?

563
00:38:12,567 --> 00:38:13,567
You're almost 30!

564
00:38:13,687 --> 00:38:15,008
What are you going to do
if you don't get married?

565
00:38:15,288 --> 00:38:15,727
